<span id="freeTextContainer15038445275837155962">In Depression-era Chicago, Harper Curtis finds a key to a house that opens on to other times. But it comes at a cost. He has to kill the shining girls: bright young women, burning with potential. Curtis stalks them through their lives across different eras until, in 1989, one of his victims, Kirby Mazrachi, survives and starts hunting him back.<br/><br/>Working with a former homicid</span>
  <span id="freeText15038445275837155962" style="display:none">In Depression-era Chicago, Harper Curtis finds a key to a house that opens on to other times. But it comes at a cost. He has to kill the shining girls: bright young women, burning with potential. Curtis stalks them through their lives across different eras until, in 1989, one of his victims, Kirby Mazrachi, survives and starts hunting him back.<br /><br />Working with a former homicide reporter who is falling for her, Kirby races against time and reason to unravel an impossible mystery.</span>
