<div id="review_840166813" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/840166813" />
    <a title="Stephen King" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/26367680-stephen-king"><img alt="Stephen King" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442438813p2/26367680.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/840166813?book_show_action=true">Jan 31, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stephen King" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stephen King" href="/user/show/26367680-stephen-king">Stephen King</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer840166813" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7586544118657080162">No, not the twins from the Kubrick movie, but the targets of a serial killer who finds a time portal in Chicago during the Depression and jackrabbits his way through recent American history, killing women and taking trophies. Until, that is, he encounters a tuff girl who’s not so easy to do away with. It’s the black-hole version of The Time Traveler’s Wife.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

